subject: ComfyUI-Static-Primitives
question: What does ComfyUI-Static-Primitives add to ComfyUI?
answer: ComfyUI-Static-Primitives adds Static Primitives to ComfyUI to work with reroute nodes.

subject: ComfyUI-Static-Primitives
question: How do I install ComfyUI-Static-Primitives?
answer: To install ComfyUI-Static-Primitives, clone the repo inside your custom_nodes folder using `git clone https://github.com/80sVectorz/ComfyUI-Static-Primitives.git`.

subject: ComfyUI-Static-Primitives
question: What is the purpose of the static primitives in ComfyUI?
answer: The static primitives in ComfyUI are intended to simplify the workflow by providing predefined types that work with reroutes, reducing wire spaghetti.

subject: ComfyUI-Static-Primitives
question: What types of primitives are included in ComfyUI-Static-Primitives?
answer: ComfyUI-Static-Primitives includes primitives for all the basic data types and also a collection type system with default types such as samplers and schedulers.

subject: ComfyUI-Static-Primitives
question: Can I add my own collection primitives to ComfyUI-Static-Primitives?
answer: Yes, you can add your own collection primitives to ComfyUI-Static-Primitives by following the instructions found in the README file located at https://github.com/80sVectorz/ComfyUI-Static-Primitives/blob/main/collection_primitives/collection_primitives_readme.md.

subject: ComfyUI-Static-Primitives
question: Are there any installation instructions for ComfyUI-Static-Primitives?
answer: Yes, the installation instructions for ComfyUI-Static-Primitives are to clone the repo inside your custom_nodes folder using `git clone https://github.com/80sVectorz/ComfyUI-Static-Primitives.git`.
